      <acqinfo id="aspace_7573bf221ef0b6dbc34f0045ea83abab">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>Gift of Irene Weir in 1935.</p>
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_69d430ca23843b4c6277419e4892c3a7">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_a91fe555b5db36900862242585e642a9">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Truman Seymour Papers. Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>
      </prefercite>
      <bioghist id="aspace_6273e5e30a7f4a41a187587fb2433f07">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Truman Seymour: instructor in drawing at West Point, brevent Major General in Civil War, amateur artist.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_2ec6762da670a0691e917ca20be67250">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The papers consist chiefly of six sketchbooks of drawings and watercolors of Italian scenes and copies of old masters made by Truman Seymour after his retirement to Italy in 1876. Also included are two notebooks from 1885.</p>
      </scopecontent>
